net.sf.mmm.persistence.base.jpa

Class JpaSequenceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.component.base.AbstractComponent
      • net.sf.mmm.util.component.base.AbstractLoggableComponent
        • net.sf.mmm.persistence.base.sequence.AbstractSequenceManager
          • net.sf.mmm.persistence.base.jpa.JpaSequenceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SequenceManager
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HibernateSequenceManager

    public abstract class JpaSequenceManager
extends AbstractSequenceManager
    This is the abstract base implementation of SequenceManager based on JPA. It uses the EntityManager to access a Sequence via native SQL.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

    • Method Detail

      • getNextValue

        public long getNextValue(Sequence sequence)
        This method gets the next value of the given sequence. The value of the Sequence is incremented on each call. Each Sequence has a minimum and a maximum value. If the maximum value is reached, it will be reset to the minimum value.
        Parameters:
        sequence - is the Sequence to get.
        Returns:
        the next value of the sequence.

      • createNextValueSql

        protected abstract String createNextValueSql(Sequence sequence)
        Creates the SQL statement to get the next value of the given Sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequence - is the Sequence to use.
        Returns:
        the SQL statement to get the next value of the given Sequence.

      • getEntityManager

        protected final javax.persistence.EntityManager getEntityManager()
        This method gets a thread-safe EntityManager. It acts as proxy to an EntityManager associated with the current thread (created when the transaction is opened e.g. via TransactionExecutor).
        Returns:
        the according EntityManager.

      • setEntityManager

        public void setEntityManager(javax.persistence.EntityManager entityManager)
        This method injects a thread-safe EntityManager instance that acts as proxy to an EntityManager associated with the current thread (created when the transaction is opened).
        Parameters:
        entityManager - is the EntityManager to inject.
